1
00:00:24,810 --> 00:00:26,641
Bjorling...

2
00:00:27,313 --> 00:00:28,974
Suliotis?

3
00:00:29,648 --> 00:00:31,809
Almost. Bjorling is easy.

4
00:00:38,991 --> 00:00:40,652
Tebaldi?

5
00:00:40,726 --> 00:00:42,990
Bingo!

6
00:00:43,062 --> 00:00:45,223
It's my turn now.

7
00:00:50,069 --> 00:00:52,629
- Don't look!
- But I'm not looking.

8
00:00:52,705 --> 00:00:54,195
Did Daddy look?

9
00:00:54,873 --> 00:00:56,363
Is that true?

10
00:01:09,288 --> 00:01:10,949
Oh, God!

11
00:01:12,725 --> 00:01:14,386
Gigli!

12
00:01:14,460 --> 00:01:17,395
That's obvious!
But what's the piece?

13
00:01:30,542 --> 00:01:31,873
Never heard it!

14
00:01:31,944 --> 00:01:33,605
Is it new?

15
00:01:34,446 --> 00:01:36,107
Seems to be.

16
00:01:37,282 --> 00:01:38,943
Well, darling?

17
00:01:47,126 --> 00:01:49,060
I'd say Handel.

18
00:01:49,128 --> 00:01:51,494
Right. But what is it?

19
00:01:54,166 --> 00:01:55,997
No idea!

20
00:02:02,541 --> 00:02:03,530
Well?

21
00:02:03,609 --> 00:02:05,941
I give up. What is it?

22
00:02:06,011 --> 00:02:07,808
Three-two to me!

23
00:02:10,816 --> 00:02:13,046
So, what is it?

24
00:02:13,886 --> 00:02:15,376
Now get your hands off!

25
00:02:15,454 --> 00:02:17,388
Just listen!

26
00:03:44,309 --> 00:03:46,140
That's cheating!

27
00:03:46,211 --> 00:03:47,200
Sorry?

28
00:03:47,279 --> 00:03:49,270
It's cheating to be practicing.

29
00:03:49,348 --> 00:03:52,511
We've booked for 10:00
tomorrow morning. You are coming?

30
00:03:53,685 --> 00:03:54,913
Yes, sure.

31
00:04:00,325 --> 00:04:01,917
We'll put the boat in the water first.

32
00:04:02,594 --> 00:04:05,927
Can you give us a hand?
Let's say, in 20 minutes?

33
00:04:09,768 --> 00:04:12,202
Sure! Yes, I'll be there in 20 minutes.

34
00:04:12,271 --> 00:04:14,102
Okay. Thanks.

35
00:04:14,172 --> 00:04:15,662
See you in a tick.

36
00:04:24,950 --> 00:04:26,781
What's up with him?

37
00:04:26,852 --> 00:04:28,012
No idea.

38
00:04:28,086 --> 00:04:29,576
He seems in a huff.

39
00:04:29,655 --> 00:04:31,816
She didn't say a word.

40
00:04:31,890 --> 00:04:34,051
Who did you arrange
to play with tomorrow?

41
00:04:34,126 --> 00:04:35,457
Her.

42
00:04:35,527 --> 00:04:36,892
Yesterday?

43
00:04:36,962 --> 00:04:38,623
The day before.

44
00:04:38,697 --> 00:04:39,629
Well?

45
00:04:40,465 --> 00:04:42,126
Nothing. She was totally normal.

46
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:44,532
Sissi isn't there.

47
00:04:44,603 --> 00:04:47,595
Maybe she was just in the house.
Or at the beach.

48
00:04:49,474 --> 00:04:51,442
Who were the two laddies?

49
00:04:52,110 --> 00:04:53,270
How should I know?

50
00:04:53,345 --> 00:04:57,281
They're probably relatives.
I think his brother has a son that age.

51
00:05:33,785 --> 00:05:36,777
Don't put that there!
Take your things upstairs!

52
00:05:36,855 --> 00:05:37,844
Okay.

53
00:05:37,923 --> 00:05:39,254
Do it now!

54
00:05:39,324 --> 00:05:42,157
Don't leave things in the entrance,
or someone will trip over.

55
00:05:42,227 --> 00:05:45,719
There's still so much left in the car.

56
00:05:45,797 --> 00:05:47,788
Are you listening?

57
00:05:47,866 --> 00:05:49,731
I'm going!

58
00:05:50,235 --> 00:05:53,227
Open the windows, will you.
We need to let some air in.

59
00:05:53,305 --> 00:05:55,239
Okay, Mom!

60
00:06:02,247 --> 00:06:04,841
Stop it, Rolfi! Stop it!

61
00:06:04,916 --> 00:06:06,747
Go on, get down!

62
00:06:06,818 --> 00:06:08,683
I have to unpack!

63
00:06:09,921 --> 00:06:11,786
Go on, get out!

64
00:06:13,792 --> 00:06:15,760
- Georg?
- Yes?

65
00:06:15,827 --> 00:06:17,692
Where's the other box
with the food?

66
00:06:18,864 --> 00:06:20,195
I'll bring it right away.

67
00:06:20,265 --> 00:06:23,291
The golf gear was in the way.
I put it in the Rover last.

68
00:06:24,670 --> 00:06:29,403
We'd better get them in quick!
The things have got really hot!

69
00:06:29,474 --> 00:06:32,466
This cool-box is totally useless.

70
00:06:32,544 --> 00:06:35,707
Stop it now, you'll knock me over.

71
00:06:35,781 --> 00:06:37,510
- The butter's all soft.
- Go see your mistress.

72
00:06:38,517 --> 00:06:40,849
There're some cold cuts in the other box.

73
00:06:40,919 --> 00:06:43,046
I'll get it. I'll just open the windows.

74
00:06:45,223 --> 00:06:48,556
Leave the shutters closed on the lake side,
or it'll be too hot.

75
00:06:48,627 --> 00:06:52,620
Stop that. You'll get something
in a minute, I must just put this away.

76
00:06:52,698 --> 00:06:56,862
Can't you call the dog?
He won't let me put the things away.

77
00:06:56,968 --> 00:06:58,367
Rolfi!

78
00:06:58,403 --> 00:06:59,461
Come here!

79
00:06:59,538 --> 00:07:00,698
Come and see your master!

80
00:07:00,772 --> 00:07:04,606
And the bottles too,
otherwise it'll all be warm by the evening.

81
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:09,941
Stop it, Rolfi!

82
00:07:10,015 --> 00:07:11,505
Be quiet!

83
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:13,740
Come in!

84
00:07:14,653 --> 00:07:16,746
Sorry. He's off his head.

85
00:07:16,822 --> 00:07:18,312
Come in!

86
00:07:19,324 --> 00:07:20,586
Hello.

87
00:07:20,659 --> 00:07:23,492
Thanks for coming.
It'd have been tough on our own.

88
00:07:23,562 --> 00:07:26,395
- No problem! This is...
- Paul. Nice to meet you.

89
00:07:26,465 --> 00:07:28,194
Paul is son of a business colleague.

90
00:07:28,266 --> 00:07:31,599
- It's a pleasure. Nice of you to help.
- Mine too.

91
00:07:31,670 --> 00:07:33,331
I mean, the pleasure's mine.

92
00:07:34,506 --> 00:07:37,566
- Not so much his.
- Will you be quiet?

93
00:07:37,642 --> 00:07:38,802
Lunatic!

94
00:07:38,877 --> 00:07:41,345
- Get into the house, go on!
- Come here, Rolfi!

95
00:07:42,347 --> 00:07:44,645
- When did you get out here?
- Last week.

96
00:07:45,150 --> 00:07:45,980
You too?

97
00:07:46,051 --> 00:07:47,484
- Yes.
- No.

98
00:07:47,552 --> 00:07:50,282
They didn't arrive till the weekend.
We came on Friday.

99
00:07:52,124 --> 00:07:53,455
Hello, Fred!

100
00:07:53,525 --> 00:07:55,618
Nice of you to come over right away.

101
00:07:57,629 --> 00:08:00,120
- How's Eva?
- Fine.

102
00:08:00,999 --> 00:08:02,660
- Hello.
- Hello, madam.

103
00:08:03,702 --> 00:08:05,192
...and where's Tropea?

104
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:07,329
In south Italy. Right at the tip,

105
00:08:07,405 --> 00:08:10,397
- almost on the toes of the boot.
- But it's even hotter there.

106
00:08:10,475 --> 00:08:12,136
Not necessarily.

107
00:08:12,210 --> 00:08:16,374
Last year when I was in Italy it was freezing
and here you were swimming, right?

108
00:08:16,448 --> 00:08:20,248
But it's a shame Sissi isn't here.
Without her, it's...

109
00:08:20,919 --> 00:08:22,648
- Be careful!
- I am!

110
00:08:22,721 --> 00:08:25,053
Careful, or the overhauling
will have been for nothing.

111
00:08:25,123 --> 00:08:27,114
Look, you can't see anything!

112
00:08:27,192 --> 00:08:28,181
Good.

113
00:08:29,194 --> 00:08:31,219
Can you help me lift the boom over?

114
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:36,590
Mind the halyard!

115
00:08:50,949 --> 00:08:53,941
But she said she'd be there
for the whole holiday.

116
00:08:54,019 --> 00:08:58,183
Listen, my boy.
I don't know why she isn't there either.

117
00:08:58,290 --> 00:09:01,782
Maybe she went to Tropea
with a school friend. I don't know.

118
00:09:01,827 --> 00:09:05,160
Tomorrow we'll go over and ask
her mother. She's bound to explain all.

119
00:09:05,230 --> 00:09:06,891
Now stop moping...

120
00:09:06,965 --> 00:09:09,126
Why was Uncle Fred so strange?

121
00:09:09,201 --> 00:09:11,362
I'm not surprised!

122
00:09:11,436 --> 00:09:14,030
She got pretty worked up
about it last time.

123
00:09:14,706 --> 00:09:16,401
Forget it, please.

124
00:09:17,642 --> 00:09:20,338
She won't change,
and you'll just get in a state.

125
00:09:21,179 --> 00:09:22,441
Exactly!

126
00:09:23,114 --> 00:09:24,809
That's it!

127
00:09:26,318 --> 00:09:28,809
Great. They're outside
working on the boat.

128
00:09:31,256 --> 00:09:32,587
What?

129
00:09:33,725 --> 00:09:36,558
5:00 or 5:30.
I don't know the time here,

130
00:09:36,628 --> 00:09:38,459
I mean, the kitchen clock has stopped.

131
00:09:38,530 --> 00:09:40,725
I must get a new battery on Monday.

132
00:09:42,667 --> 00:09:43,998
What?

133
00:09:44,069 --> 00:09:45,832
Yes, that's what I'm doing now.

134
00:09:46,571 --> 00:09:48,300
Some fillets.

135
00:09:49,140 --> 00:09:52,974
Yes, you know, it's crazy. The whole thing
defrosted and now it needs eating.

136
00:09:53,879 --> 00:09:55,870
Come out and see us!

137
00:09:55,947 --> 00:09:59,940
No, really, like a fool, I froze
three pounds of beef fillet at once,

138
00:10:00,018 --> 00:10:02,179
and now here I am.

139
00:10:02,254 --> 00:10:05,815
No, I'm not joking.
Come and spend the weekend.

140
00:10:06,658 --> 00:10:07,590
What?

141
00:10:07,659 --> 00:10:10,127
He shouldn't make such a fuss.
Hold on.

142
00:10:10,795 --> 00:10:12,956
We need a sharp knife.

143
00:10:16,501 --> 00:10:18,560
I'd like to see it again some day.
Tell Dad.

144
00:10:18,637 --> 00:10:19,968
Sorry.

145
00:10:20,038 --> 00:10:22,529
Tell your beloved to pack up his laptop,

146
00:10:22,607 --> 00:10:25,770
get in the car, and you'll be here
in two hours at the most!

147
00:10:27,712 --> 00:10:29,577
He shouldn't be so elusive.

148
00:10:31,182 --> 00:10:32,843
Okay. Think about it.

149
00:10:32,918 --> 00:10:35,318
In any case,
there's enough steak here for a week.

150
00:10:37,355 --> 00:10:38,515
Bye, Fanny.

151
00:10:38,590 --> 00:10:40,751
Say, give us another ring anyway

152
00:10:40,825 --> 00:10:43,419
to tell us whether we can expect you.

153
00:10:43,495 --> 00:10:44,985
Yes, bye.

154
00:10:45,063 --> 00:10:47,361
- What is it now?
- Someone's here.

155
00:10:47,432 --> 00:10:49,366
- Where?
- At the door.

156
00:10:53,939 --> 00:10:54,871
Hello?

157
00:10:54,940 --> 00:10:57,067
Hello. Sorry to disturb you.

158
00:10:57,175 --> 00:10:58,665
I'm from next door.

159
00:10:58,710 --> 00:11:01,645
We saw each other
when you stopped the car at the gate.

160
00:11:01,713 --> 00:11:03,374
Oh, yes, we did.

161
00:11:04,516 --> 00:11:06,177
Come in, please.

162
00:11:07,352 --> 00:11:10,014
Hurry up, we're eating in 10 minutes!

163
00:11:10,088 --> 00:11:11,578
So what is it?

164
00:11:11,656 --> 00:11:13,146
Well...

165
00:11:13,224 --> 00:11:14,885
Eva sent...

166
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:16,951
I mean, Mrs. Berlinger sent me.

167
00:11:17,028 --> 00:11:18,518
She's just cooking...

168
00:11:19,264 --> 00:11:23,564
and she's run out of eggs.
She wonders if you can help her out.

169
00:11:23,635 --> 00:11:25,398
But of course.

170
00:11:25,470 --> 00:11:27,199
- How many does she need?
- Four.

171
00:11:27,939 --> 00:11:28,928
Four?

172
00:11:29,641 --> 00:11:31,939
- What for?
- Sorry?

173
00:11:32,010 --> 00:11:33,500
What for?

174
00:11:33,578 --> 00:11:35,569
What does she need the eggs for?

175
00:11:35,647 --> 00:11:37,308
I mean, what's she making?

176
00:11:37,382 --> 00:11:39,373
No idea.

177
00:11:40,118 --> 00:11:42,279
Are they okay like that
or shall I wrap them?

178
00:11:42,954 --> 00:11:44,444
As you like.

179
00:11:45,123 --> 00:11:46,954
So how did you get in?

180
00:11:47,025 --> 00:11:49,516
At the front.
I mean, by the beach.

181
00:11:49,594 --> 00:11:51,755
But you didn't get wet at all!

182
00:11:51,830 --> 00:11:53,320
There's a hole in the fence,

183
00:11:53,398 --> 00:11:54,888
by the water, not in the water.

184
00:11:54,966 --> 00:11:56,160
Fred knows -

185
00:11:56,234 --> 00:11:59,499
I mean, Mr. Berlinger knows it.
He showed me it.

186
00:11:59,604 --> 00:12:00,935
I see. Okay.

187
00:12:00,972 --> 00:12:02,633
So, wrapped, or is this okay?

188
00:12:02,707 --> 00:12:04,641
No, no, that's fine, no problem.

189
00:12:04,709 --> 00:12:06,677
- Many thanks.
- You're welcome.

190
00:12:09,581 --> 00:12:12,072
Love to Eva.
Look forward to the golf tomorrow!

191
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:14,015
I'll tell her. Thanks again.

192
00:12:14,085 --> 00:12:16,576
And thanks again to Fred
and your friend -

193
00:12:16,654 --> 00:12:19,145
- Damn it!
- What's up?

194
00:12:25,296 --> 00:12:26,786
It's not a disaster.

195
00:12:26,865 --> 00:12:28,526
Hang on.

196
00:12:42,814 --> 00:12:44,873
Thank God, we just arrived...

197
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:48,212
and I must shop
in the village on Monday.

198
00:12:48,286 --> 00:12:49,844
I'm really embarrassed.

199
00:12:49,921 --> 00:12:53,413
It's nothing. No one here eats eggs
for breakfast anyway,

200
00:12:53,491 --> 00:12:55,482
so it's not a major problem.

201
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:57,494
That's a relief, thank you.

202
00:12:58,663 --> 00:13:01,154
I should just have been more careful.

203
00:13:02,133 --> 00:13:05,830
- I put my left hand -
- Well, no point in crying over spilt milk.

204
00:13:05,904 --> 00:13:07,235
You're really kind.

205
00:13:07,305 --> 00:13:09,068
One does one's best.

206
00:13:17,048 --> 00:13:18,538
I'm really sorry.

207
00:13:22,787 --> 00:13:24,482
I'm very clumsy, you know.

208
00:13:25,824 --> 00:13:28,258
I think I've got two left hands.

209
00:13:28,326 --> 00:13:30,658
So you're ideal for carrying eggs.

210
00:13:30,728 --> 00:13:32,662
Yes, you could say.

211
00:13:34,165 --> 00:13:35,928
Well...

212
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,468
And what are we going to do now?

213
00:13:42,474 --> 00:13:46,137
We do have steak,
but we might be getting visitors,

214
00:13:46,211 --> 00:13:48,645
and they're bound to want eggs
for breakfast.

215
00:13:49,481 --> 00:13:51,676
But you'll have four left.

216
00:13:54,185 --> 00:13:57,177
After all, I did see
you had a box of twelve, right?

217
00:13:58,323 --> 00:14:00,655
You're right.

218
00:14:14,772 --> 00:14:16,433
Shouldn't I wrap them up?

219
00:14:16,508 --> 00:14:18,169
No need.

220
00:14:18,243 --> 00:14:19,403
Are you sure?

221
00:14:19,477 --> 00:14:21,308
If you want to.

222
00:14:21,379 --> 00:14:23,040
If I want to?

223
00:14:23,114 --> 00:14:25,173
Well, maybe it is better after all.

224
00:14:28,153 --> 00:14:30,485
- Oh, no!
- What's the matter?

225
00:14:32,657 --> 00:14:34,318
Oh, no!

226
00:15:06,591 --> 00:15:08,081
I'm sorry.

227
00:15:09,594 --> 00:15:14,588
Before you destroy the rest of the kitchen,
maybe you should take your eggs and leave.

228
00:15:16,434 --> 00:15:17,924
Well...

229
00:15:21,940 --> 00:15:23,771
Here you are.

230
00:15:23,841 --> 00:15:25,433
Won't you wrap them?

231
00:15:42,293 --> 00:15:44,557
I'm really sorry.

232
00:15:45,396 --> 00:15:46,886
Honestly.

233
00:15:46,965 --> 00:15:48,455
Me too.

234
00:15:55,206 --> 00:15:56,434
There.

235
00:15:56,507 --> 00:15:59,169
- Here you are.
- Many thanks. Thank you.

236
00:15:59,277 --> 00:16:01,211
I'll tell Mrs. Berlinger how nice you were.

237
00:16:01,246 --> 00:16:03,339
Okay. Do as you see fit.

238
00:16:03,414 --> 00:16:05,575
- Bye.
- Good-bye.

239
00:17:09,414 --> 00:17:11,075
Excuse me?

240
00:17:21,592 --> 00:17:22,923
Stop it! Rolfi!

241
00:17:22,994 --> 00:17:24,484
Excuse me!

242
00:17:26,264 --> 00:17:28,232
Off you go!

243
00:17:28,299 --> 00:17:29,960
Get lost!

244
00:17:30,034 --> 00:17:31,865
I mean now!

245
00:17:34,939 --> 00:17:37,806
I'm sorry. He's completely harmless.

246
00:17:37,875 --> 00:17:40,366
- He just wants to have a game.
- Funny game.

247
00:17:41,045 --> 00:17:42,706
Did he hurt you?

248
00:17:42,780 --> 00:17:44,441
Peter's just afraid of dogs.

249
00:17:44,515 --> 00:17:46,710
- I'm sorry.
- Me too.

250
00:17:46,784 --> 00:17:48,775
He jumped up on me.

251
00:17:48,853 --> 00:17:50,514
I'm sorry about that.

252
00:17:50,588 --> 00:17:52,249
Well.

253
00:17:52,323 --> 00:17:54,314
Shall I lock him in so you can leave?

254
00:17:54,392 --> 00:17:56,417
- No need.
- I can tell my husband to -

255
00:17:56,494 --> 00:17:58,485
There's really no need, thanks.

256
00:17:58,596 --> 00:18:01,258
It's my fault.
I quite forgot the dog.

257
00:18:01,299 --> 00:18:03,460
Otherwise, I'd have come to fetch the...

258
00:18:04,202 --> 00:18:05,863
Oh! What a wonderful kit!

259
00:18:05,937 --> 00:18:07,598
Gallaway, isn't it?

260
00:18:10,842 --> 00:18:12,503
It's fantastic.

261
00:18:12,577 --> 00:18:14,135
May I?

262
00:18:15,012 --> 00:18:17,378
We hardly stand a chance for tomorrow!

263
00:18:19,217 --> 00:18:21,014
Good clubs don't make good golfers.

264
00:18:21,686 --> 00:18:23,347
That's true, yes.

265
00:18:25,022 --> 00:18:27,923
Would it be cheeky of me
to ask if I can try it just once?

266
00:18:28,926 --> 00:18:31,087
Right now, outside?

267
00:18:31,162 --> 00:18:32,424
Please! Okay?

268
00:18:32,497 --> 00:18:34,488
From the lawn out to the lake, okay?

269
00:18:36,367 --> 00:18:38,198
- If it makes you happy. I -
- Thanks.

270
00:18:43,474 --> 00:18:44,964
Excuse me.

271
00:18:45,543 --> 00:18:47,374
He loves golf!

272
00:18:47,445 --> 00:18:49,413
- We both do.
- Sorry?

273
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:51,311
Both of us. We both love golf.

274
00:19:06,364 --> 00:19:07,729
Rolfi!

275
00:19:07,799 --> 00:19:09,391
Stop it!

276
00:19:09,467 --> 00:19:11,128
Rolfi!

277
00:19:11,202 --> 00:19:12,863
Be quiet now!

278
00:19:14,338 --> 00:19:15,703
What's up?

279
00:19:15,773 --> 00:19:18,606
I don't know,
probably it's too hot for him too.

280
00:19:37,295 --> 00:19:39,286
I'll go and see.

281
00:19:52,977 --> 00:19:54,808
Brilliant!

282
00:19:54,879 --> 00:19:57,211
Like the difference
between day and night.

283
00:19:58,616 --> 00:20:00,106
Thanks very much.

284
00:20:00,184 --> 00:20:01,674
You're welcome.

285
00:20:03,354 --> 00:20:05,288
Where's Tom?

286
00:20:05,356 --> 00:20:07,517
- Who?
- Did you give him the eggs?

287
00:20:07,592 --> 00:20:09,116
Sorry?

288
00:20:12,663 --> 00:20:14,597
The driver is absolutely top-class.

289
00:20:14,665 --> 00:20:15,996
You must try it.

290
00:20:16,067 --> 00:20:17,227
Listen, young man.

291
00:20:17,301 --> 00:20:21,362
I don't know what game you're playing,
but I'm not going to join in.

292
00:20:23,674 --> 00:20:25,164
Will you go now, please?

293
00:20:29,313 --> 00:20:30,803
What game?

294
00:20:31,883 --> 00:20:35,148
Sorry, madam, but I don't understand
why you're suddenly so unfriendly.

295
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:39,983
Have Tom or I
done anything to annoy you?

296
00:20:40,057 --> 00:20:41,991
Please, would you leave?

297
00:20:43,594 --> 00:20:46,290
Did you behave badly while I was outside?

298
00:20:46,964 --> 00:20:48,898
Was he cheeky?

299
00:20:48,966 --> 00:20:51,833
- Did he say anything -
- That's enough.

300
00:20:53,638 --> 00:20:56,038
I asked you to leave, so...

301
00:20:56,107 --> 00:20:57,768
please go.

302
00:20:58,843 --> 00:21:00,003
Okay.

303
00:21:00,945 --> 00:21:04,403
I don't understand what's upset you so,
but if you insist...

304
00:21:04,482 --> 00:21:06,143
Fine.

305
00:21:08,119 --> 00:21:10,952
Give the eggs to Tom
and we won't bother you again.

306
00:21:11,022 --> 00:21:12,683
I'm sorry?

307
00:21:12,757 --> 00:21:15,248
Of course we'll be telling Eva and Fred.

308
00:21:15,326 --> 00:21:18,693
Honestly, I've never experienced
anything like it before.

309
00:21:19,363 --> 00:21:21,194
What about you, Tom?

310
00:21:25,369 --> 00:21:27,564
May we have the eggs now, please?

311
00:21:28,472 --> 00:21:30,804
I told you to leave!

312
00:21:30,875 --> 00:21:32,809
Did I do something wrong...

313
00:21:32,877 --> 00:21:34,868
Now just get out of here, you...

314
00:21:34,946 --> 00:21:36,937
Is the dog with you?
What's going on?

315
00:21:37,014 --> 00:21:39,175
- Get them out!
- Good to see you, Mr. Schober.

316
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:40,740
You are Mr. Schober, right?

317
00:21:40,818 --> 00:21:42,809
Fred, I mean, Mr. Berlinger told me.

318
00:21:42,887 --> 00:21:45,185
What?
What's the matter?

319
00:21:45,256 --> 00:21:47,747
- Throw him out!
- Your wife's mistaken.

320
00:21:47,825 --> 00:21:49,486
I'm very glad you're here.

321
00:21:49,560 --> 00:21:51,721
I'm sure you can clarify
the misunderstanding.

322
00:21:51,796 --> 00:21:54,788
- Daddy, I can't -
- Please, Georg!

323
00:21:59,136 --> 00:22:01,730
It's outrageous!

324
00:22:02,740 --> 00:22:05,504
Can I explain how this
misunderstanding arose?

325
00:22:05,576 --> 00:22:08,739
Mrs. Berlinger sent me over
to fetch some eggs.

326
00:22:08,813 --> 00:22:10,303
So what? And then?

327
00:22:10,381 --> 00:22:13,714
Your wife gave the eggs to Peter,
but he smashed them.

328
00:22:13,784 --> 00:22:16,878
Yes. And she gave me
four more eggs, but...

329
00:22:16,954 --> 00:22:19,115
then the dog jumped up on me...

330
00:22:19,190 --> 00:22:20,680
and now...

331
00:22:20,758 --> 00:22:23,591
But it was a 12-pack,
and you're shopping Monday anyway...

332
00:22:23,661 --> 00:22:25,652
We just want the eggs,

333
00:22:25,730 --> 00:22:27,220
that's all.

334
00:22:27,898 --> 00:22:30,059
Can you tell me what's going on?

335
00:22:39,477 --> 00:22:40,967
Give them the eggs.

336
00:22:41,045 --> 00:22:43,206
Hold on!
Can you wait a moment?

337
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:45,305
- Can I take them?
- Just a moment.

338
00:22:45,383 --> 00:22:47,044
What's going on?

339
00:22:47,118 --> 00:22:50,610
It can't just be about these ridiculous eggs.
Why this rage?

340
00:22:50,688 --> 00:22:53,179
I'm not justifying myself to these...

341
00:22:54,358 --> 00:22:57,987
I asked you to throw them out.
I must have my reasons.

342
00:23:00,331 --> 00:23:02,663
Do as you wish.
For me, the subject is closed.

343
00:23:02,733 --> 00:23:03,893
Anna?

344
00:23:08,272 --> 00:23:09,933
Would you please leave?

345
00:23:10,441 --> 00:23:12,602
My wife doesn't feel well.

346
00:23:15,279 --> 00:23:19,511
I can't act as arbitrator in a matter
I don't know anything about.

347
00:23:19,583 --> 00:23:21,244
Please, would you leave?

348
00:23:28,259 --> 00:23:29,749
What is it?

349
00:23:29,827 --> 00:23:31,317
If you don't mind?

350
00:23:33,497 --> 00:23:35,465
So give them to him!

351
00:23:35,533 --> 00:23:37,194
What's going on?

352
00:23:37,268 --> 00:23:39,259
Nothing's going on.

353
00:23:39,336 --> 00:23:42,669
She gave him the eggs,
the dog jumped on him, he smashed them.

354
00:23:42,740 --> 00:23:45,072
He wants more.
Is it so complicated?

355
00:23:45,142 --> 00:23:46,973
What kind of tone is that supposed to be?

356
00:23:47,645 --> 00:23:49,306
Watch I don't smash your balls as well!

357
00:23:53,317 --> 00:23:55,979
Now get out! Right now!

358
00:24:00,591 --> 00:24:02,081
Is it broken?

359
00:24:05,262 --> 00:24:07,594
Be good, now.

360
00:24:07,665 --> 00:24:09,155
Behave yourself!

361
00:24:12,269 --> 00:24:13,930
Be nice!

362
00:24:14,004 --> 00:24:15,995
I don't want to hurt you,
but behave yourself!

363
00:24:21,278 --> 00:24:23,212
Please stay where you are.

364
00:24:23,280 --> 00:24:24,770
Please stay there!

365
00:24:26,450 --> 00:24:29,146
- He hit me in the face.
- Yes. He started it.

366
00:24:30,988 --> 00:24:33,479
You can help him if you want,
but no messing about.

367
00:24:35,493 --> 00:24:37,654
- Bring him a chair.
- My knee!

368
00:24:37,728 --> 00:24:40,720
- He should take off his pants and sit down.
- A chair!

369
00:24:40,798 --> 00:24:43,289
Peter studies medicine. He'll fix it.

370
00:24:43,367 --> 00:24:45,528
Take off your pants, please.

371
00:24:55,846 --> 00:24:58,713
If you won't let me see your wound,
I can't help you.

372
00:24:58,816 --> 00:25:01,046
Sorry I hurt you,

373
00:25:01,085 --> 00:25:04,020
but you left me no choice,
you must admit.

374
00:25:05,189 --> 00:25:08,420
Be reasonable, Mr. Schober.
Let him look at your leg.

375
00:25:08,492 --> 00:25:10,323
He's sure to be able to help.

376
00:25:12,797 --> 00:25:14,458
Will you leave please?

377
00:25:14,532 --> 00:25:15,726
Please!

378
00:25:17,067 --> 00:25:18,728
This won't get us anywhere.

379
00:25:18,803 --> 00:25:21,636
You must let him help you.
You haven't any choice.

380
00:25:22,606 --> 00:25:24,597
You're a ship's captain, sir.

381
00:25:25,376 --> 00:25:28,675
You know that on board ship,
the Captain's word is final.

382
00:25:29,346 --> 00:25:31,337
So, what do you want to do, sir?

383
00:25:32,183 --> 00:25:34,845
Do you want to call someone?
An ambulance?

384
00:25:34,919 --> 00:25:36,409
Or the police?

385
00:25:37,154 --> 00:25:40,487
Go on! I won't stop you.
Nor will Tom.

386
00:25:40,558 --> 00:25:42,287
That's a promise!

387
00:25:42,359 --> 00:25:43,018
Right?

388
00:25:48,332 --> 00:25:49,993
What are you waiting for?

389
00:25:57,341 --> 00:25:59,901
He dropped the mobile in the water.

390
00:26:09,954 --> 00:26:11,615
Why are you doing this?

391
00:26:11,689 --> 00:26:13,179
Why not?

392
00:26:14,458 --> 00:26:16,551
Okay, then, another game.

393
00:26:17,228 --> 00:26:19,196
A guessing game.

394
00:26:20,564 --> 00:26:22,225
What's this?

395
00:26:36,981 --> 00:26:38,312
A golf ball.

396
00:26:38,382 --> 00:26:40,907
Exactly, sir, a golf ball.

397
00:26:41,986 --> 00:26:44,147
And why do I have it here in my pocket?

398
00:26:47,224 --> 00:26:49,158
The lady knows.

399
00:26:49,226 --> 00:26:50,887
Because...

400
00:26:53,998 --> 00:26:55,659
Well?

401
00:26:58,969 --> 00:26:59,799
Well?

402
00:27:01,071 --> 00:27:03,232
- Because you didn't hit it.
- Exactly!

403
00:27:03,307 --> 00:27:05,468
And why didn't I hit it?

404
00:27:05,542 --> 00:27:06,941
Because you were stopped.

405
00:27:07,011 --> 00:27:08,000
Exactly.

406
00:27:08,746 --> 00:27:10,577
And because I had to test
the club another way.

407
00:27:22,793 --> 00:27:24,818
Where is he?

408
00:27:24,895 --> 00:27:26,226
Cold.

409
00:27:28,132 --> 00:27:29,622
Cold.

410
00:27:30,367 --> 00:27:31,959
Colder.

411
00:27:34,471 --> 00:27:35,631
Cold.

412
00:27:53,057 --> 00:27:54,115
Warmer.

413
00:27:54,191 --> 00:27:55,783
Warmer.

414
00:27:58,095 --> 00:28:00,256
Hotter.

415
00:28:00,331 --> 00:28:01,662
Cold.

416
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:24,210
Really cold.

417
00:28:33,464 --> 00:28:35,625
Warmer, hotter, boiling!

418
00:28:59,823 --> 00:29:02,451
Would you kindly get me
some food from the kitchen?

419
00:29:03,627 --> 00:29:05,117
Would it be possible?

420
00:29:12,936 --> 00:29:15,427
Bananas or something like that.

421
00:29:17,775 --> 00:29:21,267
And don't think of picking up
a knife or something.

422
00:29:21,345 --> 00:29:23,176
I'd be sorry if you did.

423
00:29:23,247 --> 00:29:24,737
For your sake.

424
00:29:35,759 --> 00:29:38,250
The sun's coming out again.

425
00:29:42,933 --> 00:29:45,458
Very kind of you. Thank you.

426
00:30:01,151 --> 00:30:02,812
Hello! Sweetie!

427
00:30:06,790 --> 00:30:08,724
Where are you?

428
00:30:10,994 --> 00:30:13,155
Come on down!

429
00:30:14,498 --> 00:30:17,331
We're both thinking the same, aren't we?

430
00:30:22,673 --> 00:30:24,732
We saw your boat!

431
00:30:25,375 --> 00:30:28,276
Hello, Gerda!
Hello, Robert!

432
00:30:28,345 --> 00:30:31,007
How long have you been here?

433
00:30:31,081 --> 00:30:32,571
Not long.

434
00:30:32,649 --> 00:30:35,584
We're still unpacking.

435
00:30:35,652 --> 00:30:37,745
How long are you staying?

436
00:30:37,821 --> 00:30:39,652
A week or two.

437
00:30:39,723 --> 00:30:41,384
We're not sure yet.

438
00:30:41,458 --> 00:30:42,789
Great!

439
00:30:42,860 --> 00:30:45,624
- Hello, darling, lovely to see you.
- Hello.

440
00:30:51,702 --> 00:30:53,363
Have you met my sister?

441
00:30:53,437 --> 00:30:55,871
No! Pleased to meet you!

442
00:30:55,939 --> 00:30:57,099
Hello, Robert!

443
00:30:57,207 --> 00:30:58,902
- Everything okay?
- Of course.

444
00:31:01,378 --> 00:31:04,779
This is Paul.
He's living with our neighbors.

445
00:31:04,848 --> 00:31:07,180
- Hello, Paul!
- Hello, pleased to meet you!

446
00:31:07,251 --> 00:31:09,185
Are you cold?

447
00:31:09,253 --> 00:31:11,915
No, I have eczema.

448
00:31:11,989 --> 00:31:15,152
You should go swimming.
The water here does wonders for you.

449
00:31:15,225 --> 00:31:16,556
Thank you for the tip.

450
00:31:16,627 --> 00:31:17,992
Hello.

451
00:31:18,061 --> 00:31:19,028
How's Georg?

452
00:31:19,696 --> 00:31:21,254
Very well, thank you!

453
00:31:21,331 --> 00:31:22,821
So where is he?

454
00:31:22,900 --> 00:31:25,232
He pulled a muscle putting the mast up.

455
00:31:25,302 --> 00:31:26,792
So he's lying down.

456
00:31:26,870 --> 00:31:28,360
That's a real shame.

457
00:31:28,438 --> 00:31:30,599
That's the result of doing
everything yourself.

458
00:31:30,674 --> 00:31:35,008
Robert wouldn't dream of putting our boat
in the water on his own, right?

459
00:31:36,847 --> 00:31:39,213
Tell your beloved to pull
himself together.

460
00:31:39,283 --> 00:31:42,275
We barbecue nearly every night.
We can't do without him.

461
00:31:42,352 --> 00:31:44,013
I'll tell him!

462
00:31:44,087 --> 00:31:47,420
I mean it. As soon as he's better,
come and see us right away.

463
00:31:47,491 --> 00:31:50,892
Robert's son is here with his girlfriend.
He'll like her.

464
00:31:51,728 --> 00:31:53,059
Right then.

465
00:31:54,364 --> 00:31:55,854
Have a good time, darling.

466
00:31:55,933 --> 00:31:58,265
If the wind doesn't change, bring the car.

467
00:31:58,368 --> 00:32:00,302
The weather forecast says wind.

468
00:32:00,337 --> 00:32:02,430
For tomorrow.

469
00:32:02,506 --> 00:32:05,168
- I said to Robert we'd get nowhere.
- Where are you moored?

470
00:32:05,242 --> 00:32:06,732
What?

471
00:32:06,810 --> 00:32:09,540
Oh! Over there,
behind the headland.

472
00:32:09,613 --> 00:32:10,773
But on the other side.

473
00:32:12,115 --> 00:32:14,948
- The wooden house covered in ivy?
- That's it.

474
00:32:15,018 --> 00:32:18,112
- It looks very pretty.
- Indeed it is, young man.

475
00:32:18,188 --> 00:32:20,019
Right then. Bye!

476
00:32:26,496 --> 00:32:29,056
- Are you staying all week?
- This week, sure.

477
00:32:33,237 --> 00:32:34,727
Might see you tonight!

478
00:32:34,805 --> 00:32:37,740
As you like.
We're always pleased to see you!

479
00:32:38,475 --> 00:32:40,136
I don't know yet.

480
00:32:40,210 --> 00:32:43,543
- We'll see how Georg is.
- Yes, you see! See you soon!

481
00:32:47,050 --> 00:32:49,712
They'll be here
in two hours at the latest...

482
00:32:49,786 --> 00:32:51,617
and then this farce will be over.

483
00:32:51,688 --> 00:32:53,519
Sorry, but that's not quite true.

484
00:32:53,590 --> 00:32:55,888
I heard the end of your phone call.

485
00:32:55,959 --> 00:32:59,895
You asked your friends to call you back
if they were coming tonight.

486
00:32:59,997 --> 00:33:01,487
Or did I misunderstand you?

487
00:33:01,531 --> 00:33:04,056
Even if they can't reach us,
they'll still come.

488
00:33:04,134 --> 00:33:05,761
Is lying allowed?

489
00:33:06,670 --> 00:33:08,160
Just a moment!

490
00:33:13,877 --> 00:33:15,367
There you are. Please.

491
00:33:16,713 --> 00:33:19,045
You really can speak to us openly.

492
00:33:19,116 --> 00:33:22,950
You'll feel much better.
We're also being very open with you.

493
00:33:27,624 --> 00:33:30,457
Perhaps try putting a cushion under it.

494
00:33:31,628 --> 00:33:34,654
If you'd accepted Peter's help,
it would be hurting less.

495
00:33:36,833 --> 00:33:38,994
I'm quite willing to help you.

496
00:33:39,069 --> 00:33:41,230
But I don't want to impose.

497
00:33:45,309 --> 00:33:46,936
Careful!

498
00:33:48,445 --> 00:33:51,471
Yes, raise the leg.
That's bound to be more comfortable.

499
00:33:55,152 --> 00:33:57,484
There we are! Done!

500
00:33:58,822 --> 00:34:00,653
Can you leave it out, you bastards?

501
00:34:02,359 --> 00:34:03,849
Is that an offer?

502
00:34:03,927 --> 00:34:05,417
- What?
- Using our first names?

503
00:34:11,268 --> 00:34:13,099
I'm very happy about that.

504
00:34:13,170 --> 00:34:16,105
It does vastly simplify our communication.

505
00:34:17,774 --> 00:34:20,436
I'd still like to apologize for just now,

506
00:34:20,510 --> 00:34:22,444
for being too familiar,

507
00:34:23,113 --> 00:34:27,607
but you must admit that the smack was
an unreasonable reaction nonetheless.

508
00:34:30,487 --> 00:34:31,818
Paul.

509
00:34:35,625 --> 00:34:37,616
This is Peter.

510
00:34:39,162 --> 00:34:41,824
Come here, Tom.
Have you no manners?

511
00:34:41,898 --> 00:34:43,559
Give Georg your hand.

512
00:34:45,635 --> 00:34:47,296
Here, it's for the pain.

513
00:34:47,371 --> 00:34:49,896
What? To you, we're non-existent?

514
00:34:49,973 --> 00:34:52,305
- Being on familiar terms doesn't mean -
- You bastard...

515
00:35:09,259 --> 00:35:11,489
Quiet! Please!

516
00:35:11,561 --> 00:35:12,721
Stop!

517
00:35:14,898 --> 00:35:18,061
Stop it now, otherwise your mother
will get it, do you understand?

518
00:35:20,404 --> 00:35:21,393
Understand?

519
00:35:27,110 --> 00:35:28,771
Keep quiet now.

520
00:35:38,288 --> 00:35:40,950
What a scene,
just for being on first-name terms!

521
00:35:54,638 --> 00:35:57,004
We were only trying to improve relations.

522
00:35:57,908 --> 00:36:00,172
- I thought we could -
- Why are you doing that?

523
00:36:03,180 --> 00:36:04,841
Fatty, why are you doing that?

524
00:36:09,586 --> 00:36:11,076
Go on, tell us!

525
00:36:12,589 --> 00:36:15,649
I don't know. I...

526
00:36:15,725 --> 00:36:17,215
The Captain wants to know.

527
00:36:17,294 --> 00:36:18,124
Why?

528
00:36:19,463 --> 00:36:20,760
Well?

529
00:36:24,935 --> 00:36:27,495
It's difficult to talk about it. I...

530
00:36:27,571 --> 00:36:29,061
Don't be shy.

531
00:36:30,807 --> 00:36:32,775
You know just how hard it is...

532
00:36:33,710 --> 00:36:36,144
My God, what a fuss!

533
00:36:36,813 --> 00:36:38,576
His father got a divorce...

534
00:36:38,648 --> 00:36:40,138
when he was still that tiny,

535
00:36:41,117 --> 00:36:43,449
- and he took another woman -
