where this lovely rifle comes from.

770
00:59:32,924 --> 00:59:34,482
Or does it seem familiar?

771
00:59:34,993 --> 00:59:37,188
Haven't you ever been hunting with Fred?

772
00:59:39,364 --> 00:59:42,527
Do you know, your little darling
just tried to kill me with it?

773
00:59:45,537 --> 00:59:49,701
Scarcely believable, but it's the truth,
and nothing but the truth.

774
00:59:49,774 --> 00:59:51,264
Isn't that right, Georgie?

775
00:59:56,381 --> 00:59:58,042
What do you say, Tom?

776
00:59:58,116 --> 00:59:59,447
Dreadful.

777
01:00:01,386 --> 01:00:03,047
What's the time?

778
01:00:03,121 --> 01:00:05,783
Just after 11:00.

779
01:00:05,857 --> 01:00:08,826
We should start thinking about our bet,
don't you think?

780
01:00:10,995 --> 01:00:14,658
Actually we ought to be grateful
to Georgie for helping us.

781
01:00:15,333 --> 01:00:16,664
One for Beavis,

782
01:00:16,734 --> 01:00:18,497
one for Butt-Head.

783
01:00:22,273 --> 01:00:25,174
A, B, BOO and out go you!

784
01:00:25,243 --> 01:00:29,703
You're not leaving at this stage.
First you'll have to say your age.

785
01:00:32,450 --> 01:00:33,781
Well?

786
01:00:37,355 --> 01:00:38,982
She doesn't want to play.

787
01:00:39,490 --> 01:00:41,583
Well, how old do you think she is?

788
01:00:43,595 --> 01:00:45,085
37?

789
01:00:47,098 --> 01:00:48,827
No flab...

790
01:00:49,334 --> 01:00:51,029
