let's say 35.

792
01:00:55,907 --> 01:00:56,839
Agreed?

793
01:00:59,677 --> 01:01:01,008
She agrees.

794
01:01:01,079 --> 01:01:03,070
Who are you going to start counting with?

795
01:01:03,781 --> 01:01:04,713
Her?

796
01:01:09,187 --> 01:01:11,678
And now I'm going to
get myself something to eat.

797
01:01:13,358 --> 01:01:15,019
One, two, three,

798
01:01:15,093 --> 01:01:17,186
four, five, six, seven...

799
01:01:33,711 --> 01:01:35,645
Can I get anyone anything?

800
01:02:12,317 --> 01:02:14,251
You're an idiot, Fatty.

801
01:02:14,319 --> 01:02:17,686
You don't shoot the person you've
counted out, but the one that's left over!

802
01:02:17,755 --> 01:02:19,086
What's wrong with you?

803
01:02:19,157 --> 01:02:21,318
- He tried to escape!
- So what?

804
01:02:21,392 --> 01:02:23,553
That's no reason
to get trigger-happy.

805
01:02:23,628 --> 01:02:25,118
Have you no sense of timing?

806
01:02:25,964 --> 01:02:27,454
What's the time?

807
01:02:27,532 --> 01:02:29,295
Just before 12:00.

808
01:02:29,367 --> 01:02:30,857
Shit.

809
01:02:30,935 --> 01:02:32,596
We'll get nothing from the others now.

810
01:02:33,771 --> 01:02:36,604
- Let's get out of here.
- Fine.

811
01:02:36,674 --> 01:02:40,633
Thanks so much for the driver.
I'll put it back in the bag, okay?

812
01:02:40,712 --> 01:02:41,701
Thanks.

813
01:02:42,847 --> 01:02:44,337
So, have a good evening!

814
01:02:44,415 --> 01:02:45,746
Good-bye!

815
01:02:45,817 --> 01:02:47,114
Bye!

816
01:05:11,195 --> 01:05:13,129
They've gone.

817
01:05:50,501 --> 01:05:53,163
Do you hear? They've gone!

818
01:06:36,714 --> 01:06:39,205
I'll get a knife.

819
01:08:28,192 --> 01:08:30,217
Come on.
Calm down now.

820
01:08:35,700 --> 01:08:38,032
Take deep breaths.

821
01:08:41,605 --> 01:08:43,095
Come on, darling.

822
01:08:44,375 --> 01:08:46,036
Calm down now.

823
01:08:48,713 --> 01:08:50,544
Calm yourself.

824
01:08:53,050 --> 01:08:54,381
Calm yourself.

825
01:08:54,452 --> 01:08:57,285
That's it. Take some deep breaths.

826
01:10:52,269 --> 01:10:54,601
We've got to get out of here.

827
01:10:56,440 --> 01:10:58,499
What if they come back?

828
01:11:01,178 --> 01:11:03,612
Do you think you can walk
if I support you?

829
01:11:08,552 --> 01:11:10,042
I'll try.

830
01:11:19,897 --> 01:11:22,229
What's wrong with your arm?

831
01:11:28,005 --> 01:11:32,066
Shall I try and make a splint for it?
Then I can hold you better.

832
01:11:33,744 --> 01:11:35,905
No, it's okay. Come on.

833
01:12:00,871 --> 01:12:02,361
Let's go.

834
01:12:09,446 --> 01:12:10,936
Let's go.

835
01:12:20,724 --> 01:12:22,214
Okay?

836
01:12:32,236 --> 01:12:33,897
No! Anna!

837
01:12:35,940 --> 01:12:37,305
No!

838
01:13:24,555 --> 01:13:26,216
They've locked the door.

839
01:13:27,191 --> 01:13:29,022
We must use the window.

840
01:13:29,093 --> 01:13:30,583
I can't.

841
01:13:30,661 --> 01:13:32,151
Georg!

842
01:13:32,229 --> 01:13:34,561
- Please!
- I can't manage it.

843
01:13:34,632 --> 01:13:35,792
You go.

844
01:13:35,866 --> 01:13:39,358
It's crazy wasting so much time.
Run for it. Please!

845
01:13:39,436 --> 01:13:41,267
Climb out of the kitchen window.

846
01:13:41,338 --> 01:13:43,499
Try to get as far as the inn, or...

847
01:13:43,574 --> 01:13:46,065
If we're locked in here,
the gate will be shut too.

848
01:13:47,745 --> 01:13:49,679
That's true.

849
01:13:50,514 --> 01:13:53,176
Take a pair of pliers and cut the fence.

850
01:13:53,250 --> 01:13:57,186
But careful on the road.
Maybe they're waiting out there.

851
01:13:58,689 --> 01:14:00,714
Where are the pliers?

852
01:14:03,394 --> 01:14:05,487
I don't know.

853
01:14:05,562 --> 01:14:07,553
Here, in the kitchen.

854
01:14:09,566 --> 01:14:11,056
No,

855
01:14:11,135 --> 01:14:12,659
down at the boat shed.

856
01:14:13,871 --> 01:14:15,862
I can't leave you alone here.

857
01:14:15,939 --> 01:14:17,429
Go now, please!

858
01:14:18,776 --> 01:14:20,937
Put some clothes on.

859
01:14:21,011 --> 01:14:23,502
And shoes too, so you can run.

860
01:14:29,186 --> 01:14:31,347
Hold on, the bag's still here.

861
01:14:31,422 --> 01:14:32,912
Down there.

862
01:14:45,536 --> 01:14:47,470
I'll hide down in the wine cellar.

863
01:14:48,138 --> 01:14:49,969
The key must be in the door.

864
01:14:51,909 --> 01:14:54,742
I'll shut myself in
and wait for you to come back.

865
01:14:59,750 --> 01:15:02,082
How will you get down there?

866
01:15:02,152 --> 01:15:03,642
I'll manage.

867
01:15:19,870 --> 01:15:21,804
Go now! Please!

868
01:15:42,559 --> 01:15:44,493
The mobile! It's working again!

869
01:15:44,561 --> 01:15:45,493
What?

870
01:15:45,562 --> 01:15:48,053
It's working!
It's obviously dried out.

871
01:15:48,132 --> 01:15:50,293
- So get on the phone!
- Who to?

872
01:15:50,367 --> 01:15:52,858
Anyone! The police!

873
01:15:52,936 --> 01:15:54,597
What's their number?

874
01:15:54,671 --> 01:15:56,332
No idea.

875
01:15:56,440 --> 01:15:57,805
Call my mother...

876
01:15:57,841 --> 01:15:59,809
Your father-
No, wait...

877
01:15:59,877 --> 01:16:02,539
Call Peter, he's at home,
I know, he wanted to -

878
01:16:02,613 --> 01:16:05,275
Press four and then hit speed-dial.

879
01:16:08,118 --> 01:16:09,608
It's not ringing.

880
01:16:12,122 --> 01:16:13,612
Let me listen.

881
01:16:16,794 --> 01:16:18,125
But there is a signal!

882
01:16:18,195 --> 01:16:20,356
Some of the contacts
are probably still damp.

883
01:16:39,383 --> 01:16:40,372
Nothing.

884
01:16:42,553 --> 01:16:45,215
Get the hair dryer.
Maybe it'll help.

885
01:16:46,056 --> 01:16:48,217
Can you pass me the chair?

886
01:17:15,018 --> 01:17:16,849
It won't work.

887
01:19:00,657 --> 01:19:02,147
Leave it, come on.

888
01:19:03,493 --> 01:19:05,393
Maybe it's permanently broken.

889
01:19:05,462 --> 01:19:06,952
Get going!

890
01:19:09,633 --> 01:19:13,125
We're wasting far too much time.
Let me do it.

891
01:19:15,472 --> 01:19:17,303
Go on!

892
01:19:19,810 --> 01:19:21,971
Pull me over there on the chair.

893
01:19:22,045 --> 01:19:24,536
I think it'll be easier than walking.

894
01:19:57,214 --> 01:19:58,408
Thanks.

895
01:19:59,883 --> 01:20:01,817
And now, run!

896
01:20:14,398 --> 01:20:16,366
Please, forgive me!

897
01:20:23,573 --> 01:20:25,165
It -

898
01:20:36,253 --> 01:20:38,244
I love you!

899
01:20:47,431 --> 01:20:48,921
Run, please!

900
01:22:45,081 --> 01:22:47,242
Help!

901
01:23:19,549 --> 01:23:22,040
Peter? It's Georg!

902
01:23:23,553 --> 01:23:26,488
Can you hear me?
I can barely hear you!

903
01:23:28,325 --> 01:23:30,987
Listen, if you can hear me,

904
01:23:31,061 --> 01:23:33,928
send the police over to our
lake house, right away!

905
01:23:35,665 --> 01:23:36,927
Hello?

906
01:23:37,434 --> 01:23:39,299
Shit!

907
01:23:51,081 --> 01:23:53,015
Peter! Can you hear me?

908
01:26:00,510 --> 01:26:01,670
Stop!

909
01:28:15,011 --> 01:28:16,501
Missed!

910
01:28:16,579 --> 01:28:18,069
Morning, Captain.

911
01:28:19,716 --> 01:28:21,206
Morning.

912
01:28:21,284 --> 01:28:24,117
They'll be there any minute.

913
01:28:24,187 --> 01:28:27,179
We'll have to hurry then.
Right, Beavis?

914
01:28:27,257 --> 01:28:29,088
Why don't you believe me?

915
01:28:29,158 --> 01:28:32,355
- How old did we say? 37?
- 35.

916
01:28:32,428 --> 01:28:36,489
Good that the battery
charger's in the car!

917
01:28:36,566 --> 01:28:39,000
- If it's her age, you must start with her.
- Why?

918
01:28:39,068 --> 01:28:40,899
- The battery was okay.
- That's the rules.

919
01:28:40,970 --> 01:28:42,801
Okay, I'll start with her.

920
01:28:42,872 --> 01:28:45,204
Yes, I know.

921
01:28:45,275 --> 01:28:49,211
It's time you had another idea.
The lady tried that trick before.

922
01:28:49,279 --> 01:28:50,769
Count faster, Beavis.

923
01:28:52,448 --> 01:28:54,541
Do you think we have no imagination?

924
01:28:54,617 --> 01:28:57,450
Without risk, you can't have a bet,
that's obvious, Captain.

925
01:28:57,554 --> 01:28:59,488
You must have a chance too.

926
01:28:59,522 --> 01:29:04,221
The wind blows where it wishes.
That's the joy of sailing, don't you think?

927
01:29:04,294 --> 01:29:05,625
Right then!

928
01:29:05,695 --> 01:29:07,185
...thirty-four, thirty-five!

929
01:29:07,263 --> 01:29:09,424
Don't make the same mistake again.

930
01:29:09,499 --> 01:29:12,991
It's the one that's left who's turn it is,
not the one who's counted out.

931
01:29:18,608 --> 01:29:19,540
Hang on.

932
01:29:19,609 --> 01:29:22,271
I can see a new toy.

933
01:29:23,012 --> 01:29:25,071
I assume we owe this to the lady?

934
01:29:27,250 --> 01:29:29,912
This will make things a bit more amusing.

935
01:29:31,588 --> 01:29:33,852
The dumb suffer in unspectacular fashion.

936
01:29:35,525 --> 01:29:37,356
We want to offer the audience something...

937
01:29:37,427 --> 01:29:39,486
and show what we can do, right?

938
01:29:48,705 --> 01:29:50,536
You can join in again now.

939
01:29:54,210 --> 01:29:56,701
We were already
on first-name terms, right?

940
01:29:58,214 --> 01:29:59,875
So, Anna,

941
01:30:00,783 --> 01:30:02,307
now we're going to play:

942
01:30:02,385 --> 01:30:04,819
"The Loving Wife", or...

943
01:30:04,887 --> 01:30:08,983
Whether by knife or whether by gun
Losing your life can sometimes be fun.

944
01:30:12,328 --> 01:30:13,989
Hey! No falling asleep!

945
01:30:14,664 --> 01:30:17,861
You have to play with us,
or you'll be gagged again.

946
01:30:17,934 --> 01:30:19,765
That's not very nice, is it?

947
01:30:22,705 --> 01:30:25,868
So, here are the rules of the game:

948
01:30:25,942 --> 01:30:29,139
Georgie senior has been counted out,
so it's his turn.

949
01:30:30,480 --> 01:30:32,141
It'll be hard to change that.

950
01:30:32,982 --> 01:30:35,143
Unless you want to take his place.

951
01:30:36,319 --> 01:30:37,809
Do you want to?

952
01:30:40,356 --> 01:30:43,621
I'm sure Fatty will understand.
Right, Fatty?

953
01:30:43,693 --> 01:30:45,354
Don't call me Fatty.

954
01:30:45,428 --> 01:30:49,762
- You see, he understands.
- Get this over with. That's enough.

955
01:30:49,832 --> 01:30:51,493
That's enough?

956
01:30:51,567 --> 01:30:53,228
You think that's enough?

957
01:30:55,104 --> 01:30:56,765
What do you think, Anna?

958
01:30:56,873 --> 01:30:59,205
Have you had enough?
Or do you want to play some more?

959
01:31:00,009 --> 01:31:01,601
Don't reply anymore.

960
01:31:01,678 --> 01:31:04,010
Let them do what they want. Please!

961
01:31:04,080 --> 01:31:06,241
Then it'll be over quicker.

962
01:31:06,315 --> 01:31:08,476
Huh, that's cowardly!

963
01:31:08,551 --> 01:31:11,384
We're not up to feature film length yet.

964
01:31:11,454 --> 01:31:13,388
Is that enough?

965
01:31:13,456 --> 01:31:17,256
But you want a real ending,
with plausible plot development, don't you?

966
01:31:17,326 --> 01:31:20,955
The bet is still on.
It can't be withdrawn unilaterally.

967
01:31:21,631 --> 01:31:22,723
So:

968
01:31:22,799 --> 01:31:25,199
the game is called: "The Loving Wife."

969
01:31:25,268 --> 01:31:28,601
Although Beavis has done the counting,
she can choose...

970
01:31:28,671 --> 01:31:31,162
who will be next. And...

971
01:31:31,240 --> 01:31:32,901
using what implement!

972
01:31:33,576 --> 01:31:35,737
Do we prefer the little knife?

973
01:31:35,812 --> 01:31:37,643
Or the rifle?

974
01:31:38,881 --> 01:31:41,042
Well then, what does the housewife say?

975
01:31:45,555 --> 01:31:47,546
Hello, wakey, wakey!

976
01:31:50,259 --> 01:31:53,194
So, you're not interested?

977
01:31:53,262 --> 01:31:55,355
You don't want to play anymore.

978
01:31:56,466 --> 01:31:58,627
Beavis, show her the game again.

979
01:31:58,701 --> 01:31:59,895
Wait.

980
01:31:59,969 --> 01:32:01,300
Here you are.

981
01:32:01,370 --> 01:32:02,860
Hey, careful!

982
01:32:02,939 --> 01:32:04,600
I almost cut myself.

983
01:32:04,674 --> 01:32:06,164
Really?

984
01:32:17,220 --> 01:32:20,383
You see. It's the little knife.
You can spare him that.

985
01:32:20,456 --> 01:32:22,287
You only have to play with us.

986
01:32:25,394 --> 01:32:27,055
I understand, Anna.

987
01:32:27,130 --> 01:32:28,620
I understand, really!

988
01:32:29,632 --> 01:32:32,795
It's not a good feeling,
causing the one you love to suffer.

989
01:32:34,470 --> 01:32:37,530
But it costs so little to avoid all that.

990
01:32:37,607 --> 01:32:41,099
You only need follow the rules,
and all will be well.

991
01:33:08,070 --> 01:33:09,162
What must I do?

992
01:33:12,208 --> 01:33:14,369
You see, it wasn't that difficult.

993
01:33:15,044 --> 01:33:16,807
And we'll make it easy too.

994
01:33:16,879 --> 01:33:19,040
You recite a prayer of your choice.

995
01:33:19,115 --> 01:33:23,643
If you say it flawlessly, God will help you
and you choose what happens next.

996
01:33:29,492 --> 01:33:31,824
Or shall we carry on with Georgie senior?

997
01:33:33,563 --> 01:33:34,587
I don't know a prayer.

998
01:33:36,265 --> 01:33:37,926
You don't know any prayers?

999
01:33:38,835 --> 01:33:40,735
Not a single prayer?

1000
01:33:43,172 --> 01:33:44,161
Is that possible?

1001
01:33:45,341 --> 01:33:46,831
Tell her one, Fatty.

1002
01:33:46,909 --> 01:33:48,934
Stop calling me Fatty all the time.

1003
01:33:49,011 --> 01:33:51,002
I'll stop saying it. Well?

1004
01:33:52,949 --> 01:33:55,417
Oh Lord and Father, make me kind,
So I, in heaven, my place may find.

1005
01:33:55,484 --> 01:33:58,510
- That's too easy.
- I can't think of any others.

1006
01:33:59,689 --> 01:34:00,849
Okay.

1007
01:34:00,923 --> 01:34:03,585
Oh Lord and Father, make me kind,
So I, in heaven, my place may find.

1008
01:34:05,595 --> 01:34:07,529
No! Not like that!

1009
01:34:07,597 --> 01:34:09,087
It's a prayer.

1010
01:34:09,165 --> 01:34:11,759
You can't just drone on like that.

1011
01:34:11,834 --> 01:34:14,997
You're asking the Lord God for something.
So pray properly.

1012
01:34:16,873 --> 01:34:19,341
Go on.
Go down on your knees properly.

1013
01:34:20,676 --> 01:34:22,769
Go on! Get on with it!

1014
01:34:28,117 --> 01:34:30,881
There. That's right. Kneel down properly.

1015
01:34:33,389 --> 01:34:35,323
Put your hands together.

1016
01:34:35,992 --> 01:34:37,823
Not on your stomach.

1017
01:34:37,894 --> 01:34:40,556
Where is the one you pray to?
Up there!

1018
01:34:41,464 --> 01:34:44,228
You have to pray to the heavens!
That's it!

1019
01:34:45,835 --> 01:34:49,498
Right, and now, in a fervent tone,
if you don't mind.

1020
01:34:55,711 --> 01:34:58,544
- Beavis, can you help her a little?
- No!

1021
01:35:07,189 --> 01:35:09,350
Oh Lord and Father, make me kind,

1022
01:35:11,861 --> 01:35:13,692
So I, in heaven, my place may find.

1023
01:35:13,763 --> 01:35:15,230
Well done!
You did that well!

1024
01:35:16,565 --> 01:35:20,057
That was the trial run,
and now we're going for Olympic Gold:

1025
01:35:20,136 --> 01:35:23,469
If you can recite this prayer,
which is sadly much too short,

1026
01:35:23,539 --> 01:35:26,201
from back to front, without any mistakes,

1027
01:35:26,275 --> 01:35:30,575
you can not only choose
which of you kicks the bucket first,

1028
01:35:30,646 --> 01:35:34,912
but also, and no doubt
this will interest you more - how.

1029
01:35:34,984 --> 01:35:39,250
whether quick and painless by the bullet...

1030
01:35:39,322 --> 01:35:40,789
Careful!

1031
01:35:47,263 --> 01:35:49,231
Where's the remote?

1032
01:35:50,433 --> 01:35:52,765
Where's the fucking remote control?

1033
01:36:19,028 --> 01:36:22,191
That was the trial run,
and now we're going for Olympic Gold:

1034
01:36:22,264 --> 01:36:26,098
If you can recite this prayer,
which is sadly much too short,

1035
01:36:26,168 --> 01:36:29,831
from back to front, without any mistakes,

1036
01:36:29,905 --> 01:36:32,897
you can not only choose
which of you kicks the bucket first,

1037
01:36:32,975 --> 01:36:37,309
but also, and no doubt
this will interest you more - how:

1038
01:36:37,380 --> 01:36:40,213
whether quick and painless by the bul -

1039
01:36:43,953 --> 01:36:47,787
You shouldn't have done that, Anna.
One doesn't break the rules.

1040
01:36:47,857 --> 01:36:50,690
Sorry. You've failed.

1041
01:36:54,063 --> 01:36:56,554
Say good-bye to Georgie.

1042
01:37:31,534 --> 01:37:33,525
Would you sit down?

1043
01:38:13,976 --> 01:38:15,466
Can you give me your gloves?

1044
01:38:20,616 --> 01:38:23,107
...only it's all inverted.

1045
01:38:23,185 --> 01:38:26,643
But of course all these predictions are wrong
so as to avoid a panic.

1046
01:38:26,722 --> 01:38:28,212
But now Kelvin knows how it really is...

1047
01:38:28,290 --> 01:38:31,453
and wants to warn his wife
and daughter in time.

1048
01:38:31,527 --> 01:38:35,520
But the problem is not only getting
from the world of antimatter to reality,

1049
01:38:35,598 --> 01:38:37,122
- but also to regain communication -
- Look!

1050
01:38:38,467 --> 01:38:40,162
Now that's a sporting attitude!

1051
01:38:44,373 --> 01:38:46,204
Hey, look out, fatso!

1052
01:38:46,275 --> 01:38:47,765
I thought you were a non-swimmer.

1053
01:38:56,118 --> 01:38:58,279
Go and get the widow.
She'll feel lonely otherwise.

1054
01:39:02,091 --> 01:39:03,752
Would you mind cooperating?

1055
01:39:03,826 --> 01:39:06,795
It's not easy.
Otherwise I might hurt you.

1056
01:39:12,301 --> 01:39:14,235
So. Where was I?

1057
01:39:14,303 --> 01:39:17,795
The communication problems
between matter and antimatter.

1058
01:39:17,873 --> 01:39:20,535
Exactly. As if you were in a black hole!

1059
01:39:20,609 --> 01:39:24,443
Gravitation is so strong that nothing
can escape it: absolute silence.

1060
01:39:24,513 --> 01:39:26,174
- By the way, what's the time?
- What?

1061
01:39:26,248 --> 01:39:27,738
What's the time?

1062
01:39:27,816 --> 01:39:29,306
Just after eight.

1063
01:39:29,385 --> 01:39:30,374
Already?

1064
01:39:37,359 --> 01:39:38,519
Why?

1065
01:39:38,594 --> 01:39:41,757
The deadline was at 9:00.
She had almost an hour left!

1066
01:39:41,830 --> 01:39:44,298
Firstly,
it was too hard to sail like that,

1067
01:39:44,366 --> 01:39:48,860
- and secondly, I'm starting to get hungry.
- That's true.

1068
01:40:02,218 --> 01:40:04,209
...when Kelvin overcomes gravitation,

1069
01:40:04,286 --> 01:40:06,618
it turns out that one universe is real,

1070
01:40:06,689 --> 01:40:08,850
but the other is just a fiction.

1071
01:40:08,924 --> 01:40:10,289
How does that happen?

1072
01:40:10,359 --> 01:40:13,692
What do I know! It was a kind of
model projection in cyberspace.

1073
01:40:13,762 --> 01:40:17,095
And where is your hero now?
In reality or fiction?

1074
01:40:17,166 --> 01:40:19,657
His family is in reality
and he's in fiction.

1075
01:40:19,735 --> 01:40:22,898
- But the fiction is real, isn't it?
- How do you mean?

1076
01:40:22,972 --> 01:40:25,964
- Well, you see it in the film, right?
- Of course.

1077
01:40:26,041 --> 01:40:29,340
So, it's just as real as the reality
which you see likewise, right?

1078
01:40:29,411 --> 01:40:30,537
- Crap.
- Why?

1079
01:40:59,108 --> 01:41:01,440
Is anyone awake yet?

1080
01:41:08,550 --> 01:41:10,040
Who is it?

1081
01:41:17,393 --> 01:41:18,553
Good morning to you.

1082
01:41:18,627 --> 01:41:21,118
Sorry to disturb you so early,
but I've come from Anna's.

1083
01:41:21,196 --> 01:41:22,686
And?

1084
01:41:24,033 --> 01:41:25,694
Don't you remember me?

1085
01:41:25,768 --> 01:41:28,430
Yesterday afternoon, on the jetty.
I'm Paul.

1086
01:41:28,504 --> 01:41:29,994
Oh, yes.

1087
01:41:31,206 --> 01:41:33,037
- Good morning.
- Morning.

1088
01:41:33,108 --> 01:41:36,441
Anna sent me. We had guests arrive
unexpectedly this morning...

1089
01:41:36,512 --> 01:41:39,504
and she wonders if
you could spare her a few eggs?

1090
01:41:39,581 --> 01:41:41,071
I think so.

1091
01:41:41,150 --> 01:41:42,640
Come in.

1092
01:41:42,718 --> 01:41:44,879
Wait a minute.

